  <p><strong>1. Introduction</strong><br>
Privacy Policy
1. Introduction
This privacy policy outlines how
howfarfrommydoorstep
handles your data. Weare committed to ensuring your privacy and comply with applicable dataprotection laws. We also offer the option for anonymous submissions throughour contact form, allowing you to use fake details if you wish to maintain yourprivacy
2. Data Collection
OpenStreetMap (OSM)
: We use OSM for mapping functions. OSM does not storepersonal data for map embeddings or queries made through our site.
Google Analytics
: We use Google Analytics to understand user interactions withour site. Google Analytics collects data such as your IP address, browser type,and pages visited. This helps us improve our website.
Contact Form
: We also collect personal information, such as your name andemail address, when you use our contact form. This information is sent directlyto our email for response purposes and is not stored on the website itself. If youchoose to submit anonymously, you may use fake details for your name andemail. This option is provided to ensure your privacy when you prefer not to sharepersonal information
3. Cookies
We use cookies for essential site functionality and to track usage via GoogleAnalytics. You can control cookies through your browser settings or the cookieconsent banner provided on our site.
Cookie Consent
: We provide a consent mechanism where you can explicitlyagree to non-essential cookies. You may withdraw your consent at any time byadjusting your browser settings or through our cookie consent tool.
4. Data Use
The data collected through Google Analytics is used solely for site improvementand understanding user demographics without identifying individuals.
5. Data Sharing
Data collected by Google Analytics might be shared with Google, subject to theirprivacy policies. We do not share this data with other third parties.
6. Retention
We do not retain any personal data from OSM interactions. Data from GoogleAnalytics is retained as per Google's policies; we do not have direct control over
this retention.
Contact Form Data
: Data sent via our contact form will be retained only as longas necessary for the purpose of communication, after which it will be securelydeleted unless there's a legal obligation to retain it.
7. Your Rights
Under applicable laws, you have rights to access, correct, or delete your personaldata held by us or by Google through Analytics if identifiable. You have the rightto request data portability, object to processing, restrict processing, and not besubject to automated decision-making including profiling. To exercise theserights, please contact us using the details provided. Please note that if yousubmit data anonymously or with fake details, some rights under data protectionlaws might not be applicable since the data cannot be identified as pertaining toyou.
8. Contact
For questions about our privacy practices, please contact us at
howfarfrommydoorstep@proton.me
.
9. Updates
This policy might be updated periodically to reflect changes in our practices orthe law. We encourage you to check back regularly.
10. Consent
By using our site, you consent to our data practices as described here.
11. International Data Transfers
Data collected by Google Analytics might be transferred outside of the EuropeanEconomic Area (EEA) to Google in the United States. Google provides safeguardsfor these transfers through mechanisms like the EU-US Data Privacy Frameworkor Standard Contractual Clauses to ensure compliance with data protection laws.
